info.description: This is the spring-boot restful api for the First Pass Yield mobile application
info.title: YieldAPI

post.summary: to be refactored approves or declines pending user access request
post.description:
It should use insertAccessRequest method
This API approves or declines a pending user access request. Identification is based on SSO and Factory. Other parameters provided will be ignored. The API ticks 'pending' parameter of the request to false

Exampe input into the body:
giving all rights:
{
	 "administrator": true,
	 "dataCorrection": true,
	 "dataInput": true,
	 "factoryId": "factory_0",
	 "firstName": "Bobby",
	 "lastName": "Dylan",
	 "picViewer": true,
	 "reports": true,
	 "userSso": "100000001"
}
revoking all rights:
{
	 "administrator": false,
	 "dataCorrection": false,
	 "dataInput": false,
	 "factoryId": "factory_0",
	 "firstName": "Charles",
	 "lastName": "Chaplin",
	 "picViewer": false,
	 "reports": false,
	 "userSso": "100000001"
}

post.summary: to be refactored inserts a new access request for a user in a factory
post.description:
It should use insertAccessRequest method
This API inserts a new access request for a user in a factory. Only one access request is allowed for one user in a factory at the same time.

Exampe input into the body:
giving all rights:
{
	 "administrator": true,
	 "dataCorrection": true,
	 "dataInput": true,
	 "factoryId": "factory_0",
	 "firstName": "Bobby",
	 "lastName": "Dylan",
	 "picViewer": true,
	 "reports": true,
	 "userSso": "100000001"
}
You can revoke your request with XXXXXXXXXXXX API

post.summary: modifies the rights of a user
post.description:
This API modifies the rights of a user in a factory to do administration, modify data etc. Identification is based on SSO and Factory. Other parameters will be overwrited as they are provided in the input JSON.

Exampe input into the body:
giving all rights:
{
	 "administrator": true,
	 "dataCorrection": true,
	 "dataInput": true,
	 "factoryId": "factory_0",
	 "firstName": "Bobby",
	 "lastName": "Dylan",
	 "picViewer": true,
	 "reports": true,
	 "userSso": "100000001"
}
revoking all rights:
{
	 "administrator": false,
	 "dataCorrection": false,
	 "dataInput": false,
	 "factoryId": "factory_0",
	 "firstName": "Charles",
	 "lastName": "Chaplin",
	 "picViewer": false,
	 "reports": false,
	 "userSso": "100000001"
}

post.summary: creates a new inspection
post.description:
This function creates a new inspection in the table - it does not contain any pieceinspections or faults yet. For that use submitpieceinspections
Exampe input into the body:
input:
{
	 "factoryid" : "factory_0",
	 "assemblyNumber" : "119E7640GXXX",
	 "jobNumber" : "jobNumber",
	 "fpy" : "InProgress",
	 "userSso" : "212589603",
}

post.summary: creates a new pieceinspection
post.description:
This function creates a new inspection in the table - it requires an existing inspection.
Exampe input into the body:
(use faultCodeId 2000 for Localhost and 4000 for dev server)
input:
{
	"inspectionId": 18,
	"pieceInspections": [
		 {
			    "statusHasFault": "true",
			    "createdby": "105044932",
			    "piecelabelvalue": "piecelabelvalue",
			    "customfieldheader1value": "fieldheader1value_1",
			    "customfieldheader2value": "fieldheader2value_1",
			    "pieceFaults": [
				        {
					        "faultCodeId": 4000,
					        "operatorId": 1,
					        "customfieldnc1value": "fieldnc1vaule_1_1",
					        "customfieldnc2value": "fieldnc1vaule_1_1",
					        "comments": "comment_1_1"
				        },
				        {
					        "faultCodeId": 4001,
					        "operatorId": 2,
					        "customfieldnc1value": "fieldnc1vaule_1_2",
					        "customfieldnc2value": "fieldnc2vaule_1_2"
			          }]
		 },
		 {
			    "statusHasFault": "false",
			    "pieceFaults": [],
			    "createdby": "105044932",
			    "modifiedby": "105044932"
		 }
	 ]}
}

post.summary: uploads a file to the database with autogenerated name
post.description:
This API receives an image and a json with image data.
JSON input:{ "uploadId":"upllllll" }

Postman does not support mixed request, so test it from Terminal:

curl -i -X POST -H "Content-Type: multipart/mixed" \
-F "uploadParams={"uploadId":"upllllll"};type=application/json" \
-F "file=@/Users/somahargitai/Downloads/mini.jpg" http://localhost:7001/yieldapi/services/uploadFile

curl -i -X POST -H "Content-Type: multipart/mixed" \
-F "uploadParams={"uploadId":"upllllll"};type=application/json" \
-F "file=@/Users/somahargitai/Downloads/mini.jpg" http://dev-pwr-vsite-app.pw.ge.com/yieldapi/services/uploadFile
